{{Quote|I can't begin to give you a full list of tyrants like Nom Anor that I've dealt with.''"<br />"''And of course, there was was Icknya&mdash;|Leia Organa Solo and C-3PO|<ref name="NJO">''[[The New Jedi Order: Vector Prime]]''</ref>}}
'''Icknya''' was a tyrant.<ref name="NJO" /> At some point after she became the [[Chief of State (New Republic)/Legends|Chief of State]] of the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]]<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|II|76|Icknya}}</ref> in [[11 ABY/Legends|11 ABY]],<ref name="TNEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] had to deal with Icknya.<ref name="CSWE" /> In [[25 ABY/Legends|25 ABY]],<ref name="TERC">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' dates the events of ''[[The New Jedi Order: Vector Prime]]'' to [[25 ABY/Legends|25 ABY]].</ref> the [[Protocol droid/Legends|protocol droid]] [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] compared the tyrant to the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] agent [[Nom Anor]], the ruler of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Rhommamool/Legends|Rhommamool]].<ref name="NJO" />

==Behind the scenes==
Icknya was first mentioned in the [[1999]] novel [[The New Jedi Order: Vector Prime|''Vector Prime'']], written by [[R. A. Salvatore]] as the first volume in the ''[[Star Wars: The New Jedi Order]]'' novel series.<ref name="NJO" />

